By Kunle Akinrinade  Suspected hoodlums were said to have vandalised two cars behind a building on Onifade Street, New Oko Oba area of Lagos. The incident happened in wee hours of penultimate Sunday. It was said that the hoodlums vandalised the cars taking away items such as the brain box, car radio sets and car batteries among other items. The vandalised Toyota Corolla cars, marked FST 824 and SMK 834 FL belong to some residents identified as Christopher and Ademola Taiwo. ‘’ The hoodlums came around 5am and some security dogs were barking at them but they still managed to carry out their criminal act,’’ said a source who asked not to be named. 